Merafe Resources, Metorex and Santam: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-01T05:15:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/merafe-resources-metorex-and-santam-south-african-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index advanced for
a second day, gaining 306.50, or 1 percent, to 32,272.09 at the
5 p.m. close in Johannesburg, taking its gain in the month to
2.8 percent.    Merafe Resources Ltd . (MRF SJ): The ferrochrome-mining
company reports results for the 12 months through December.
Merafe said on Jan. 27 it was expecting to report earnings per
share of between 10 cents and 12 cents, compared with a loss per
share of 6 cents for the year earlier. Merafe rose 5 cents, or
3.2 percent, to 1.60 rand.    Metorex Ltd . (MTX SJ): The copper and cobalt mining company
publishes an earnings statement for the 18 months through Dec.
31. Metorex, which changed its financial year end to December
from June, said on Feb. 11 it expected earnings per share to be
as high as 1.03 rand for the period. The stock gained 6 cents,
or 1.1 percent, to 5.70 rand.    Santam Ltd . (SNT SJ): South Africa’s largest property and
casualty insurer releases earnings for the year through
December. Santam said it expects per share earnings for the
period to be as much as 55 percent higher than the year earlier,
according to a Feb. 16 trading update. The stock climbed 3.43
rand, or 2.8 percent, to 127.96 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) jumped 1.6 percent to $27.03.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) added 0.7 percent to $48.84. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) rose 0.6 percent to $79.31. DRDGold Ltd.
(DROOY US) gained 0.4 percent to $4.77. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) advanced 1.6 percent to $17.91. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY
US) climbed 0.9 percent to $11.78. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) gained 2.1 percent to $29.43. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
rose 3.9 percent to $5.35. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) fell 0.5 percent
to $54.87.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net . 